Given the following scheduling problem:
You are an expert at scheduling meetings. You are given a few constraints on the existing schedule of each participant, the meeting duration, and possibly some preferences on the meeting time. Note there exists a solution that works with existing schedule of every participant. Here are a few example tasks and solutions:

TASK: You need to schedule a meeting for Jose, Keith, Logan, Megan, Gary and Bobby for half an hour between the work hours of 9:00 to 17:00 on Monday. 

Here are the existing schedules for everyone during the day: 
Jose has meetings on Monday during 11:00 to 11:30, 12:30 to 13:00; 
Keith has meetings on Monday during 14:00 to 14:30, 15:00 to 15:30; 
Logan is busy on Monday during 9:00 to 10:00, 12:00 to 12:30, 15:00 to 15:30; 
Megan has blocked their calendar on Monday during 9:00 to 10:30, 11:00 to 12:00, 13:00 to 13:30, 14:30 to 16:30; 
Gary has blocked their calendar on Monday during 9:00 to 9:30, 10:00 to 10:30, 11:30 to 13:00, 13:30 to 14:00, 14:30 to 16:30; 
Bobby is busy on Monday during 11:00 to 11:30, 12:00 to 12:30, 13:00 to 16:00; 

Jose do not want to meet on Monday after 15:30. Find a time that works for everyone's schedule and constraints. 
SOLUTION: 
Your solution should always have three things: the day to meet, the start time, and the end time.
Your output should be a string that starts with 'SOLUTION:' followed by three lines in this exact format:
Day: <day>
Start Time: <HH:MM> (24-hour format)
End Time: <HH:MM> (24-hour format)
Write a Python program that solves it using the Z3 solver. Always surround your final code with ```python
YOUR_CODE
```.
